“Rick has an immeasurable wealth of experience and knowledge as an acting coach. I have been a student of his for the past 13 years, and I still look forward to each of our sessions, as there is always something new to learn. He cares deeply for his students, and has the ability to adapt to each of their individual needs. The experience is always positive, and you can always trust that Rick will be there for you in your corner when you need him. I can’t wait to prep my next role with him!” - @realdarrenmann 

Can't help but feel a burst of pride as I read the testimonial from my talented actor turned family, Darren Mann. Watching you grow and excel in your acting journey has been an incredible privilege. It's more than just a collaboration; it's a genuine bond that's transformed us into a close-knit tribe. 

Our journey together reminds me of the magic that happens when actors become like family. It's about trust, support, and shared dreams. Darren, you've not only given life to characters on screen but also enriched our lives off-screen. Grateful for the moments we've crafted and excited for the future ones we'll create. Let's keep shining together, my friend. 😁🎬

In between fest posts, I gotta call out cinematographer @kaikrausedp and production designer Michael Clausen and their crews for the visual arc they achieved on #BreakwaterMovie. From a dingy prison cell to the raw beauty of the Outer Banks, Kai and Michael paint progressive layers of rural noir with a skill that has us feeling the tonal change without noticing it.

This shot of @realdarrenmann is on the expressive end, and I love it.

The one scene Kai didn’t shoot was operated by legendary underwater DP Pete Romano, ASC @hydroflexinc Watching an audience experience that action piece is a blast every time. 🌊🎥🌊
